<item>
            <title>[CXF-4476] Content-Disposition header may be incorrectly set in MTOM under windows </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-4476</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This problem can be seen in the following test case when it is executed under windows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Failed tests:   testMtomWithFileName(org.apache.cxf.systest.mtom.ClientMtomXopTest): can&apos;t get file name expected:&amp;lt;return detail + []me.bmp&amp;gt; but was:&amp;lt;return detail + &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;/C:/repos/cxf/trunk/systests/uncategorized/target/test-classes/&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;me.bmp&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is the way how the file name is extracted in AttachmentUtils.createMtomAttachmentFromDH. Concretely, this method extracts the part of the data handler&apos;s URL string after the last File.separator, where this string is given as the standard URL syntax which does not contains the windows&apos; File.separator.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;windows&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
